                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 8.029,
                                "byte_start": 85628,
                                "byte_stop": 117811,
                                "text": "The opinion of the Court in No. 97-7164, Holloway against United States will be announced by Justice Stevens."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 8.029,
                        "stop": 174.816,
                        "byte_start": 117811,
                        "byte_stop": 784874,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15060,
                            "name": "John Paul Stevens",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/john_paul_stevens",
                            "last_name": "Stevens",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2704,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 188200800,
                                    "date_end": 1277787600,
                                    "appointing_president": "Gerald Ford",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2704"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32732,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 62101,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/john_paul_stevens.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 12611,
                            "identifier": "john_paul_stevens"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 8.029,
                                "stop": 26.883,
                                "byte_start": 117811,
                                "byte_stop": 193252,
                                "text": "In 1994 the Congress amended the Federal Carjacking statute to provide that \u201cwhoever with the intent to cause death or serious bodily harm, takes a motor vehicle\u201d from another person by force and violence or by intimidation shall be guilty of the federal crime."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 26.883,
                                "stop": 48.955,
                                "byte_start": 193252,
                                "byte_stop": 281546,
                                "text": "The question in this case is one of the concerns the meaning of that definition of intent, does it require the government to prove that the defendant had an unconditional intent to kill or harm in all events or does it just require proof of an intent to kill or harm, if necessary to complete the carjacking?"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 48.955,
                                "stop": 53.749,
                                "byte_start": 281546,
                                "byte_stop": 300668,
                                "text": "The petitioner Fran\u00e7ois Holloway and an accomplice committed three carjackings."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 53.749,
                                "stop": 59.495,
                                "byte_start": 300668,
                                "byte_stop": 323656,
                                "text": "They approached each driver produced a gun and threatened to shoot unless the driver handed over the keys."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 59.495,
                                "stop": 69.163,
                                "byte_start": 323656,
                                "byte_stop": 362317,
                                "text": "The plan was to steal the cars without harming the victims, but the accomplice testified that he would have used the gun if any of the drivers had given him a hard time."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 69.163,
                                "stop": 92.319,
                                "byte_start": 362317,
                                "byte_stop": 454999,
                                "text": "At trial the District Judge instructed the jury that merely using a gun to frighten a victim was insufficient to establish an attempt to cause death or bodily harm, but the Judge continued that the government could satisfy this element if it established that the defendant intended to use the gun to cause death or serious harm in the event the alleged victim refused to turnover their cars."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 92.319,
                                "stop": 95.787,
                                "byte_start": 454999,
                                "byte_stop": 468792,
                                "text": "The jury convicted petitioner of all three carjacking counts."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 95.787,
                                "stop": 98.592,
                                "byte_start": 468792,
                                "byte_stop": 480077,
                                "text": "The Court of Appeals for the Second Circuit affirmed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 98.592,
                                "stop": 105.145,
                                "byte_start": 480077,
                                "byte_stop": 506304,
                                "text": "We granted certiorari to resolve an apparent conflict between that decision and the decision of the Ninth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 105.145,
                                "stop": 107.435,
                                "byte_start": 506304,
                                "byte_stop": 515395,
                                "text": "We now affirm."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 107.435,
                                "stop": 113.881,
                                "byte_start": 515395,
                                "byte_stop": 541204,
                                "text": "Congress enacted the carjacking statute essentially to provide a federal penalty for a particular type of robbery."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 113.881,
                                "stop": 119.666,
                                "byte_start": 541204,
                                "byte_stop": 564296,
                                "text": "The intended element of that statute thus modifies the act of taking the motor vehicle."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 119.666,
                                "stop": 137.146,
                                "byte_start": 564296,
                                "byte_stop": 634304,
                                "text": "We think that when a person points a gun at the driver, having decided to pull the trigger if the driver does not comply with the demands of the car keys, the person posses at that moment, an intent to seriously harm or kill the driver as Congress intended that term to be understood."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 137.146,
                                "stop": 150.601,
                                "byte_start": 634304,
                                "byte_stop": 688116,
                                "text": "Two considerations strongly support this conclusion: First excluding conditional attempt from the ambit of the statute, would exclude from its coverage most of the conduct that Congress obviously intended to prohibit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 150.601,
                                "stop": 158.539,
                                "byte_start": 688116,
                                "byte_stop": 719881,
                                "text": "Only in the highly unusual carjacking does the offender intend to harm or kill the driver regardless of whether the driver resists."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 158.539,
                                "stop": 170.398,
                                "byte_start": 719881,
                                "byte_stop": 767319,
                                "text": "Second, it is reasonable to presume that Congress was familiar with the cases and scholarly writing that have recognized that specific intent to commit a wrongful act maybe conditional."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 170.398,
                                "stop": 174.816,
                                "byte_start": 767319,
                                "byte_stop": 784874,
                                "text": "Justice Scalia and Justice Thomas have filed dissenting opinions."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
